docs.abstract: David Haskell, who has overseen print features and digital strategy, will step in on April 1. He plans to keep a side job as co-owner of a whiskey distillery in Brooklyn.
docs.snippet: David Haskell, who has overseen print features and digital strategy, will step in on April 1. He plans to keep a side job as co-owner of a whiskey distillery in Brooklyn.
docs.lead_paragraph: David Haskell, a longtime deputy editor at New York magazine, will become its editor in chief on April 1, inheriting a glossy biweekly and a suite of websites devoted to pursuits like fashion, food, shopping and politics. He succeeds Adam Moss, who is stepping down after 15 years at the helm.

headline.main: New York Magazine Names a New Editor as Adam Moss Departs
headline.print_headline: Magazine Promotes Its Deputy To Top Job

docs.abstract: At issue is the similarity between the name of Supermac’s, which has just over 100 outlets, and the Big Mac.
docs.snippet: At issue is the similarity between the name of Supermac’s, which has just over 100 outlets, and the Big Mac.
docs.lead_paragraph: DUBLIN — A European Union regulator has ruled that McDonald’s must give up trademark rights to one of its cornerstone products — the Big Mac — in a long-running dispute with an Irish fast-food chain called Supermac’s.

headline.main: An Irish Burger Chain Claims a Trademark Win Over McDonald’s
headline.print_headline: Irish Burger Chain Wins Its Fight With McDonald’s

docs.abstract: The automaker said its lowest-priced offering would be available only in stores or by phone, just weeks after emphasizing a shift to online sales.
docs.snippet: The automaker said its lowest-priced offering would be available only in stores or by phone, just weeks after emphasizing a shift to online sales.
docs.lead_paragraph: Faced with slumping sales and increasing financial stresses, Tesla has shifted course several times in the last two months, deciding to keep stores after saying it would close most and cutting prices before raising them again.

headline.main: Tesla Ends Online Sales of $35,000 Model 3, Creating New Hurdle for Buyers

docs.abstract: The fire, involving a Tesla sedan in a parking garage, left no one injured, the fire department said. The automaker said it had dispatched a team “at once.”
docs.snippet: The fire, involving a Tesla sedan in a parking garage, left no one injured, the fire department said. The automaker said it had dispatched a team “at once.”
docs.lead_paragraph: SHANGHAI — The electric-car maker Tesla said on Monday that it had sent a team to investigate why one of its cars appeared to spontaneously combust in Shanghai over the weekend, an incident that the authorities said had left no one hurt but that has raised fresh questions about the safety of the company’s cars.

headline.main: Tesla to Investigate Car That Appeared to Burst Into Flames in Shanghai
headline.print_headline: Tesla to Investigate Car Explosion in China

docs.abstract: Prosecutors made fresh accusations on Friday against the former Nissan chairman, setting up a legal battle that could keep him in custody for months.
docs.snippet: Prosecutors made fresh accusations on Friday against the former Nissan chairman, setting up a legal battle that could keep him in custody for months.
docs.lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Japanese prosecutors brought fresh charges of financial wrongdoing on Friday against Carlos Ghosn, the embattled global auto chief who sits in a Tokyo jail.

headline.main: Carlos Ghosn Faces New Charges in Japan as Pressure Mounts
headline.print_headline: Ex-Nissan Chief Faces Fresh Charges in Japan As Legal Battle Escalates

docs.abstract: About 15 percent of its work force will be cut, or about 200 employees across the company’s departments, including the news division.
docs.snippet: About 15 percent of its work force will be cut, or about 200 employees across the company’s departments, including the news division.
docs.lead_paragraph: BuzzFeed, often hailed as the future of publishing and a leading producer of digital content, plans to lay off 15 percent of its work force, or around 200 employees, according to a memo sent to the staff on Wednesday night.

headline.main: BuzzFeed Plans Layoffs as It Aims to Turn Profit
headline.print_headline: BuzzFeed Plans Layoffs As It Aims to Turn Profit

docs.abstract: Here’s what else we know about the billionaire Kenneth Griffin and how he spends his money (besides buying New York’s most expensive apartment).
docs.snippet: Here’s what else we know about the billionaire Kenneth Griffin and how he spends his money (besides buying New York’s most expensive apartment).
docs.lead_paragraph: Kenneth Griffin, the billionaire founder of the hedge fund Citadel, broke a real estate record on Wednesday when he closed on his purchase of a penthouse at 220 Central Park South for $238 million. It’s the highest price anyone has paid for a home in the United States, and $100 million above the previous record.Mr. Griffin went to contract on the apartment, in a building that was still being developed, in 2015 amid a real estate buying spree that includes a London mansion he bought this week for 95 million pounds, or about $122 million.

headline.main: The Hedge Fund Manager Who Just Paid $238 Million for a Manhattan Penthouse

docs.abstract: The division published best-selling books by Ta-Nehisi Coates, Trevor Noah and more. Its closing is the latest move by Penguin Random House to streamline operations.
docs.snippet: The division published best-selling books by Ta-Nehisi Coates, Trevor Noah and more. Its closing is the latest move by Penguin Random House to streamline operations.
docs.lead_paragraph: The publisher Spiegel & Grau, a Penguin Random House imprint known for its best-selling and groundbreaking nonfiction, has been shut down as part of a continuing effort to streamline Penguin Random House’s sprawling operation following the merger between Penguin and Random House in 2013.

headline.main: Penguin Random House Closes the Prestigious Imprint Spiegel & Grau
headline.print_headline: In Consolidation Move, Penguin Random House Closes Prestigious Imprint

docs.abstract: The embattled auto executive told Nikkei Asian Review that leaders at the company had sought to have him removed because of his plans to “integrate” further with Renault and Mitsubishi Motors.
docs.snippet: The embattled auto executive told Nikkei Asian Review that leaders at the company had sought to have him removed because of his plans to “integrate” further with Renault and Mitsubishi Motors.
docs.lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Carlos Ghosn, the embattled auto executive indicted on charges of financial wrongdoing, says he was the victim of “plot and treason” by other Nissan leaders who wanted to thwart his plans to bring the automaker closer to its alliance partners, Renault of France and Mitsubishi Motors of Japan.

headline.main: Carlos Ghosn Says He’s the Victim of ‘Plot and Treason’ by Rivals at Nissan
headline.print_headline: Rivals’ ‘Plot and Treason’ Toppled Him, Ghosn Says
